President Obama announced his intent to nominate the following individuals to key administration posts: Rafael Moure-Eraso for Chair of the Chemical Safety and Hazard Investigation Board, Mark A. Griffon for Member of the Chemical Safety and Hazard Investigation Board, Robert M. “Skipp” Orr for United States Executive Director of the Asian Development Bank with the Rank of Ambassador, and Carl Wieman for Associate Director for Science in the Office of Science and Technology Policy. Rafael Moure-Eraso is currently a professor and graduate coordinator at the University of Massachusetts Lowell and has extensive experience in occupational health and safety. Mark A. Griffon has worked in academia, the public sector, and the private sector, with a focus on environmental and occupational health consulting. Robert M. “Skipp” Orr has held various leadership positions in the corporate world, academia, and the U.S. government, with a specialization in Japan and international relations. Carl Wieman is a distinguished professor of physics and a Nobel laureate, known for his research in atomic and laser physics, as well as his work on science education.